reviews.text: First time! Loved it. Hot fresh, large variety of toppings & sauce  &  delicious seasonings that made it taste so good. My husband thought his was greasy from pepperoni but said tasted good. Only suggestion is real silverware.  Hard to cut with plastic.  Service excellent. Cookies pretty good. Definitely recommend

The pizza here is great. It‚Äôs quick fired, ready in minutes and bursting with flavor. We got the ‚ÄúI know it was you fredo‚Äù and added Kalamata olives. The Alfredo sauce is rich and creamy and makes a wonderful base for the pizza. There are several suggestions for pizzas, like the one we got, or you can create your own. There are all the typical toppings to choose from and then some!

We have also had the cheese sticks and the cinnamon dessert pizza and those are delicious also.

Make this a stop when you‚Äôre in the mood for a great pizza.

Next time I go for the second time I‚Äôm gonna get chicken bacon and ranch sauce. Use the ranch instead of pizza sauce. That‚Äôs always been one of my favorites all over the world next time I‚Äôll have them see if they can make it that way for me then I‚Äôll have to have a bacon, lettuce and tomatopizza from there because that oven makes it to perfection straight on the fire is the best

My wife, son (14), daughter (11), and I came for lunch (Saturday @12pm) while watching our oldest compete at Spire.

We ordered the bone- in wings ($15.49: garlic parm), Build Your Own pizza ($12.49: with chicken, bacon, garlic base, broccoli, tomatoes, and artichoke), and the Buffalo Yardbird ($14.49). The crust was crisp. The toppings were fresh. Overall, the pizzas were great. Great service from all of the staff.

The kids enjoyed watching the staff make the pizzas, giving us opportunity to modify the pizzas as we wanted.

The place was not very busy, maybe 3 other groups dining in so plenty of seating.

We paid around $60 for food, 3 drinks, and 20% tip.

Definitely will come again.

Fantastic experience. Me and my son left the spire institute and came here and bought two pizzas, an order of cheesy bread, salad, and chicken and everything was amazing.  Friendly service. Not too overpriced.

Their priced at about a dollar per ‚Äúwing‚Äú and they are the size in shape of little meatballs. Matter fact, kind of tasted like I was eating a meatball. Had it with the barbecue sauce .
